The paper discusses the robustness of machine learning algorithms against adversarial attacks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the possibility of leveraging computational hardness to achieve robustness, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
